.DS_Store
__pycache__/
*.pyc

# Release artifacts — too big for git, shipped via GitHub Releases
release/*.qcow2
release/*.tar.gz
release/*.zip
release/agent9-v*

# Plan 9 build artifacts
*.6
*.5
*.8
6.out
8.out
[0-9].out

# macOS / cross-compile artifacts (used during dev, never committed)
*.dSYM/
src/vts/test/bin/
src/pi9/pi9
src/pi9/pi9.linux.*
src/pi9/pi9.plan9.*
src/pi9/pi9.darwin.*

# Stray dev scratch
src/_restore-9front-vt/

# python9: vendored CPython source + host build are large/derived. The harness
# scripts and the parity manifests (the scoreboard) ARE committed.
python9/cpython/src/
python9/cpython/host-build/
python9/parity/manifests/*.tmp.json
# python9 cc9 profile (port/cc9/): same rule — build output and fetched upstream
# stay out, the build script + config headers are committed. deps/ holds the
# pinned tarballs build.py expects extracted there: zlib-1.3.1 and
# sqlite-amalgamation-3460100.
python9/port/cc9/_out/
python9/port/cc9/deps/
python9/release/stage/
python9/release/*.tar.gz

# hermes9: parked WIP (last touched 2026-07-08) — the LLM-agent bundle +
# launcher. Ignored FOR NOW so it stops reading as untracked noise; the tree is
# still on disk, nothing is deleted. Drop this line when it's ready to land.
# Two things to know first:
#   - pac9's registry already advertises hermes9 (and its python9 dep), but both
#     release URLs 404 — the tarballs were built and never published, so
#     `pac9 install hermes9` is broken today. Ignoring the source doesn't fix
#     that; publishing the releases does.
#   - hermes9/vendor/ is an embedded upstream clone with its own .git, so
#     `git stash -u` can't take this directory cleanly (it skips nested repos
#     and leaves vendor/ behind, splitting the tree in half).
hermes9/

# Local-only secrets and dev scratch
.env
.env.*
*.token
*.key
auth.json
